# Integration Standards

## AI / GPT Integration

### Feature Flags

```bash
AI_ENABLED=true          # Master switch for AI features
RAG_ENABLED=true         # Enable RAG search
AI_MODE=mock|openai      # Switch between stub and real API
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...    # Required when AI_MODE=openai
```

### Adapter Pattern (Ports & Adapters)

```typescript
// ✅ Always define an interface — swap implementation without touching routes
interface GptAnalysisPort {
  analyze(tender: TenderContext): Promise<AnalysisResult>;
}

class GptAnalysisAdapter implements GptAnalysisPort {
  async analyze(tender: TenderContext): Promise<AnalysisResult> {
    if (!process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY) {
      throw new Error('AI_NOT_CONFIGURED');
    }
    // call OpenAI API
  }
}

class MockGptAdapter implements GptAnalysisPort {
  async analyze(): Promise<AnalysisResult> {
    return { summary: 'Mock analysis', riskScore: 0.1 };
  }
}
```

### RAG Search

- Full-text against PostgreSQL `tsvector` (language: `spanish`)
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/rag/search?q=...`
- Frontend calls via `gptsercopService` (env flag: `VITE_ENABLE_CP_API`)
- Chunk size, overlap, and re-ranking params live in `rag.ts` — not in route files

## OCDS / Compras Públicas Data

```typescript
// Crawler: scripts/crawler/index.js
// Import: scripts/import-ocds-synthetic.ts
// Pattern: fetch → validate OCDS schema → upsert via Prisma
const response = await fetch(process.env.CRAWLER_OCDS_URL);
const ocdsRelease = await response.json();
// Always validate before insert
await db.tender.upsert({ where: { ocdsId: release.id }, ... });
```

- Source URL in `CRAWLER_*` env vars — never hardcoded
- Idempotent upserts — safe to re-run
- Log every import run to `auditLog`

## Object Storage (MinIO / S3)

```typescript
// storage.ts — presigned URL pattern
import { S3Client, GetObjectCommand, PutObjectCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-s3';
import { getSignedUrl } from '@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner';

// ✅ Never return raw S3 credentials or bucket names to clients
// ✅ Always use presigned URLs (default expiry: 15 minutes)
const url = await getSignedUrl(s3, new GetObjectCommand({ Bucket, Key }), { expiresIn: 900 });
```

Environment: `S3_BUCKET`, `S3_ENDPOINT`, `S3_ACCESS_KEY`, `S3_SECRET_KEY`

## Redis

```typescript
// redis.ts — used for health checks and optional session cache
// ✅ Check connection in /health endpoint
// ✅ Set TTL on every cache key — never store without expiration
await redis.set(`tender:${id}`, JSON.stringify(data), { EX: 3600 });
```

## Kafka (Java backend)

- Topics defined in `application.yml` → `kafka.topics.*`
- Producers: fire-and-forget for non-critical events; use `@Transactional` for DB + publish atomicity
- Consumers: idempotency key on every handler to handle at-least-once delivery
- DLQ configured for all consumer groups

## SignalR / Realtime (Frontend)

```typescript
// sercop-unified/frontend/src/realtime/
// ✅ One provider per realtime concern (notifications, live updates)
// ✅ Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff
// ✅ Must not block initial page render — load asynchronously
```

## External API Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ Wrap every external call with timeout + retry
const result = await fetchWithRetry(url, {
  timeout: 10_000,   // 10s
  retries: 3,
  backoff: 'exponential',
});

// ✅ Circuit breaker for high-traffic integrations
// ✅ Log request/response metadata (no PII) for observability
```

## Environment Configuration

All integration credentials must be in `.env` (never committed):

```bash
# AI
OPENAI_API_KEY=
AI_ENABLED=false
AI_MODE=mock

# Storage
S3_BUCKET=
S3_ENDPOINT=
S3_ACCESS_KEY=
S3_SECRET_KEY=

# Data
CRAWLER_OCDS_URL=
DATABASE_URL=
REDIS_URL=
```

Copy `.env.example` for new environments — update defaults, never hardcode.
